    Indicating verbs If a verb is a member of the Verb_set = {discuss, present, illustrate, identify, summarise, examine, describe, define, show, check, develop, review, report, outline, consider, investigate, explore, assess, analyse, synthesise, study, survey, deal, cover}, we consider the first NP following it as the preferred antecedent (scores 1 and 0).
    Empirical evidence suggests that because of the salience of the noun phrases which follow them, the verbs listed above are particularly good indicators.
    Lexically reiterated items are likely candidates for antecedent (a NP scores 2 if is repeated within the same paragraph twice or more, 1 if repeated once and 0 if not).
    Lexically reiterated items include repeated synonymous noun phrases which may often be preceded by definite articles or demonstratives.
    Also, a sequence of noun phrases with the same head counts as lexical reiteration (e.g.
    &amp;quot;toner bottle&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;bottle of toner&amp;quot;, &amp;quot